<subSubSection id="FD81B6F6BB55FFDBD42DC7A99D80FBD7" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B524E57DBB55FFDBD42DC7A99D80FBD7" blockId="2.[811,1452,477,1141]" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD42DC7A99D7BFE57" bold="true" box="[813,1075,477,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Taxonomical remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD3B9C7A99A2BFDB7" authority="Millidge, 1995" authorityName="Millidge" authorityYear="1995" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Cyphonetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD3B9C7A99C77FE57" box="[1209,1343,477,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Cyphonetria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D10A988CBB55FFDBD248C7A99A2BFDB7" author="Millidge" firstAuthor="Millidge" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" pagination="41 - 56" refId="ref4745" refString="Millidge AF (1995) Some linyphiid spiders from south-east Asia. Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society, 10: 41 - 56." type="journal article" year="1995">Millidge, 1995</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was established for a single species and based on a single female from Doi Inthanon Forest (= Doi Inthanon National Park), 
<collectingCountry id="CD8CA5EDBB55FFDBD4DFC4499D0AFDF7" box="[991,1090,573,597]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, above 
<quantity id="72634898BB55FFDBD39BC4499DBFFDF6" box="[1179,1271,573,597]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" unit="m" value="1500.0">1,500 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<bibRefCitation id="D10A988CBB55FFDBD245C4499A2EFDD7" author="Millidge" firstAuthor="Millidge" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" pagination="41 - 56" refId="ref4745" refString="Millidge AF (1995) Some linyphiid spiders from south-east Asia. Bulletin of the British Arachnological Society, 10: 41 - 56." type="journal article" year="1995">Millidge, 1995</bibRefCitation>
). Millidge did not specify which subfamily this genus belonged to, but correctly brought it closer to two other Oriental genera, 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD4E7C4E99C33FD17" authority="van Helsdingen, 1985" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" box="[999,1403,669,693]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Labullinyphia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD4E7C4E99D36FD17" box="[999,1150,669,693]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Labullinyphia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D10A988CBB55FFDBD389C4E99C33FD17" author="Helsdingen PJ van" box="[1161,1403,669,693]" firstAuthor="van Helsdingen" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" pagination="13 - 30" refId="ref4495" refString="Helsdingen PJ van (1985) Araneae: Linyphiidae of Sri Lanka, with a note on Erigonidae. Entomologica Scandinavica (Supplement), 30: 13 - 30." type="journal article" year="1985">van Helsdingen, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD42DC4CA9D56FD77" authority="Simon, 1894" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[813,1054,701,725]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Emenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD42DC4CA9AD8FD77" box="[813,912,702,725]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Emenista</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D10A988CBB55FFDBD495C4C99D56FD77" author="Simon" box="[917,1054,701,725]" firstAuthor="Simon" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" refId="ref4893" refString="Simon E (1894) Histoire naturelle des araignees, Volume 1. Roret, Paris, pp. 489 - 760." type="book" year="1894">Simon, 1894</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. These two latter genera together with 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD42BC4A99AE6FD57" authorityName="Millidge" authorityYear="1995" box="[811,942,733,757]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Cyphonetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD42BC4A99AE6FD57" box="[811,942,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Cyphonetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterised by an epigynal structure similar to the Mynogleninae-type, namely, helicoid copulatory ducts, but lacking clypeal sulci. In the absence of a described male, 
<bibRefCitation id="D10A988CBB55FFDBD474C5499D32FCF7" author="Helsdingen PJ van" box="[884,1146,829,853]" firstAuthor="van Helsdingen" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" pagination="13 - 30" refId="ref4495" refString="Helsdingen PJ van (1985) Araneae: Linyphiidae of Sri Lanka, with a note on Erigonidae. Entomologica Scandinavica (Supplement), 30: 13 - 30." type="journal article" year="1985">van Helsdingen (1985)</bibRefCitation>
assigned 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD3EFC5499CC3FCF7" authorityName="van Helsdingen" authorityYear="1985" box="[1263,1419,829,853]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Labullinyphia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD3EFC5499CC3FCF7" box="[1263,1419,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Labullinyphia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD45AC5299AACFCD7" authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1859" box="[858,996,861,885]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Linyphiinae">Linyphiinae</taxonomicName>
, noting that no erigonines were known with such a structure of the copulatory ducts. 
<bibRefCitation id="D10A988CBB55FFDBD226C5099AABFC17" author="Benjamin &amp; Hormiga" firstAuthor="Benjamin" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" pagination="161 - 181" refId="ref4333" refString="Benjamin SP &amp; Hormiga G (2009) Phylogenetic placement of the enigmatic genus Labullinyphia van Helsdingen, 1985, with redescription of Labullinyphia tersa (Simon, 1894) from Sri Lanka (Araneae: Linyphiidae). Contributions to Natural History, 12: 161 - 181." type="journal article" year="2009">Benjamin &amp; Hormiga (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, after a detailed analysis of the genitals of both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD4F0C5C99C33FC77" authority="(Simon, 1894)" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[1008,1403,957,981]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Labullinyphia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tersa">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD4F0C5C99D84FC77" box="[1008,1228,957,981]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Labullinyphia tersa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D10A988CBB55FFDBD3DEC5C99C3BFC77" author="Simon" box="[1246,1395,957,981]" firstAuthor="Simon" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" refId="ref4893" refString="Simon E (1894) Histoire naturelle des araignees, Volume 1. Roret, Paris, pp. 489 - 760." type="book" year="1894">Simon, 1894</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="6A205BDFBB55FFDBD42DC5A99A13FC57" box="[813,859,989,1013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">type</typeStatus>
species, hypothesised that this genus belonged to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD49EC5899D5FFBB7" authorityName="Emerton" authorityYear="1882" box="[926,1047,1021,1045]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erigoninae">Erigoninae</taxonomicName>
. I agree with that opinion for the time being. It seems highly likely that 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD389C2699C46FB97" authorityName="Millidge" authorityYear="1995" box="[1161,1294,1053,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Cyphonetria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD389C2699C46FB97" box="[1161,1294,1053,1077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Cyphonetria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD240C26A9CEBFB97" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1894" box="[1344,1443,1054,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Emenista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87EF396FBB55FFDBD240C26A9CEBFB97" box="[1344,1443,1054,1077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">Emenista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the genera with the rather similar genitalia, could also be assigned to the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="729B9EFEBB55FFDBD34BC2299D8CFBD7" authorityName="Emerton" authorityYear="1882" box="[1099,1220,1117,1141]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Erigoninae">Erigoninae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD81B6F6BB55FFDBD42DC2E99DB1FB17" box="[813,1273,1181,1205]" pageId="2" pageNumber="214" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B524E57DBB55FFDBD42DC2E99DB1FB17" blockId="2.[813,1273,1181,1205]" box="[813,1273,1181,1205]" pageId="2" pageNumber="214">
